<div class="content_well top">
	<div class="the_hub_content_wrapper the_hub_article">
		<div class="the_hub_content">
		<a href="/category/the-hub/" class="header_link">
		<div class="the_hub_title_wrapper">
			<div class="the_hub_logo">
				<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lit-horn.svg">
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_title">
				<h1>The Hub</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_slogan">
				<h1>News, Notes, Talk</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		</a>
		
				<div class="the_hub_item">
			<div class="banner_img">
				<a href="https://lithub.com/trumps-nea-is-terminating-hundreds-of-grants-in-literature-theater-and-the-arts/" title="Trump’s NEA is terminating hundreds of grants in literature, theater, and the arts.">
		    		<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/neh-crowbar.jpg" alt="" class="post_ft entry_post"/>
		    	</a>
			</div>
			
			<div class="post_content">
				<h1 data-report-url="/trumps-nea-is-terminating-hundreds-of-grants-in-literature-theater-and-the-arts/"><a href="https://lithub.com/trumps-nea-is-terminating-hundreds-of-grants-in-literature-theater-and-the-arts/">Trump’s NEA is terminating hundreds of grants in literature, theater, and the arts.</a></h1>
				
				<div class="author_info">
					<div class="author_photo"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/james-folta-scaled-e1711473313743-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/james-folta-scaled-e1711473313743-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="James Folta" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></div>
					<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/jamesfolta/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">James&nbsp;Folta</span></a></div>
					<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
					<div class="publish_date">May 5, 2025, 2:22pm</div>
				</div>
				
				<p>In the last few days, publications, theater groups, arts organizations, and many other National Endowment of the Arts grant recipients have been notified that their funding has been “terminated” or “withdrawn.” 41 of the 51 Literary Arts grantees in the 2025 publishing category have received a form letter about their grants, despite some having already received payments. Even some Literary Arts grants that are open from previous years have also received termination letters, reflecting this administration&#8217;s one-shiv-fits-all approach.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DJPYPmLxNYw/?img_index=1" class="external" target="_blank">N+1</a>, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DJNWwJvPQCQ/" class="external" target="_blank">The Public Theater</a>, and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DJMqzyHyZGR/?img_index=1" class="external" target="_blank">Transit Books</a> posted online about their funding cancellations, but the emerging list of affected organizations is staggering: the Hub City Writer Project, the Center for the Art of Translation, The Oxford American, the Alice James Poetry Cooperative, Nightboat Books, One Story, Red Hen Press, AGNI Magazine, Arte Publico Press, Words Without Borders, ZYZZYVA, The Common, Electric Lit, Milkweed Editions, The Paris Review, Aunt Lute Books, Bennington Review, River Styx magazine, BOA Editions, and too many other literary, theater, and dance groups. <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1cHCTXssMWuMweRLUjGQKtsck_rg7v4tMg7cpfzDQil8/htmlview#" class="external" target="_blank">There’s a shared document tracking grantees who have lost funding,</a> and it’s growing longer every time I refresh it.</p>
<p>Transit Books shared the letter they received, which is one of two form terminations that I’ve seen:</p>
<blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/DJMqzyHyZGR/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:500px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);">
<div style="padding:16px;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DJMqzyHyZGR/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;" target="_blank" class="external"> </p>
